reviews_data.review_text:
Walked in and .all outside tables were dirty with plates and or dirty glasses. Not wiped down. Went inside to grab some water and a napkin to wipe off my own table.The bar tender said they were understaffed but he cleaned off the table and was super pleasant. Ordered a mimosa, beer, tacos and fries. The drinks arrived but the the mimosa was unrecognizable. Thinking that I had been given the pineapple juice I went to the bar and said I had never had a mimosa that tasted like what had arrived at the table. I've been around 60 years so know what to expect from a half way decent mimosa.They made another one and it turns out the Orange juice was the cheapest orange juice I have ever tasted. The food arrived pretty quickly and the fries were fine the tacos were a weird texture ( burnt ends) tasting nothing like burnt ends. It tasted more like something that had been in a
crock pot for days. No one came to the table to check on us but I ventured inside to serve MYSELF some additional ketchup. There were 4 servers at the bar including two additional bar tenders. I've worked in the restaurant industry and there was no shortage of staff. Then a team of three servers came out to clean a high top but failed to wipe the table down or notice that the adjoining table was both dirty with dishes. The manager finally came by. I told him the above and he did apologize. With this lack of service and below average food and drinks I doubt that this joint will be in business for long. The only area that seemed short staffed was the kitchen but the managed to get food out really quickly. They are about five steps below Arby's or Applebee's......not that I frequent either one of these establishments. Good luck staying open with all the great restaurants and breweries in the area
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Ric,

Thank you for your feedback. We’re sorry to hear that your experience didn’t meet your expectations. We strive to provide a high level of service and hospitality to every guest, and it’s disappointing to learn that this wasn’t your impression. 

To clarify, our team was fully staffed during your visit. While one team member may have misspoken, we were operating with our standard service levels. Our bartender promptly cleared your table, replaced your drink and our manager personally checked in with you to address your concerns. 

We also want to note that we put great care into the ingredients we use, our food and beverage menus are designed with quality in mind, and we emphasize fresh, thoughtfully sourced and as many natural products as possible. 

While we may not be the right fit for everyone, we’re proud of the experience we offer and remain committed to serving our guests with intention & integrity. 

We appreciate you giving us a try and wish you best in your future dining experiences.

Cheers,
- Management

reviews_data.review_text:
I’ve given this restaurant two chances, and unfortunately, both visits had the same disappointing issues. The service is unprofessional, and the servers come off as arrogant, often making odd facial expressions that make the experience uncomfortable.

On my most recent visit, I ordered tuna tacos but was given a grilled chicken sandwich instead. Since I didn’t have much time, I just went with it, but the server didn’t even bring me silverware only my two friends received theirs. The service continued to be dismissive, and when it was time to pay, I used Apple Pay. A new server made a condescending face as if I didn’t know how to use it, which was unnecessary and rude.

As for the food, it was far from fresh. I took half of my meal home, but when I tried to eat it less than an hour later, it tasted awful stale and just downright unpleasant.

Overall, this place has bad service, unfriendly staff, and food that isn’t even fresh. Definitely not worth the time or money.

Had a wonderful lunch experience!  Server, Sydney, is fantastic! This was our first visit and Sydney eagerly explained everything about food and beverage items. We learned some of the history about how the brewery began and plans for future expansion. Our food was delicious. Sodas are served only in bottles because the owner feels they are more all natural ingredients. Beers are brewed off site, but served draft style from kegs. Well drinks and wines are also available. Coffee comes from the Coffee Shop attached to the restaurant. Coffee is brewed from HEX Coffee, a local business. Restrooms are actually individual stalls, in keeping with the Suffolk horse theme. Bar stools and chairs are comfy leather, also keeping with the equestrian theme. There are ample indoor and outdoor seating areas. Outdoor seating is in an all-season decor setting. This place has  kid friendly menus, and there are posters announcing Kids Outdoor Concerts. Looking forward to visiting their new location opening soon near Birkdale Village.

The food was pretty dang good, too. We had the tuna nachos, and these are a MUST HAVE appetizer. They were delicious. My main dish - the hot chicken sandwich - was extremely spicy. I was surprised that such a hot sandwich was offered to the general public. It came to me in a puddle of red oil and was basically too spicy to eat, I could not finish it because my mouth was on fire.

My wife ordered the salmon and roasted carrot salad and loved it.

Overall, the food and service was mostly pretty good - but the front of the house needs some help. Oh, and tone down the spice on the hot chicken sandwich, please.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Matt

We greatly appreciate this feedback. You are right, we are still ironing out some bugs but our service standards are very high and I am disappointed that we didn't do a better job to begin your experience. We will certainly make a strong effort to eliminate mistakes like this. I am pleased to hear that you enjoyed your food and overall service. I can assure you that we can and will improve on all the areas you mentioned
